All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClientActions
    Class to perform changes on the client state, primarily things that have to do with communication with the father or other nodes.
    Common
    Contains shared variables and functions for the tool
    FileEntry
    Entries for the file in the files table and results table
    HandleClient
    Handles a single incoming client or child connection to receive requests or commands.
    HLSApplication
    Represents the top level of the application, not much to see here.
    HLSController
    Handles all of the GUI interactions from the user.
    Listener
    Thread for listening for incoming conversations
    LocationList
    Represents a list of locations for a file entry.
    OutgoingTalker
    Sends outgoing messages asynchronously to the father
